96/*
97 * finalize a provider shared library, it's no longer usable.
98 * however, there might still be keys referencing this provider,
99 * so the actual freeing of memory is handled by pkcs11_provider_unref().
100 * this is called when a provider gets unregistered.
101 */
102static void
103pkcs11_provider_finalize(struct pkcs11_provider *p)
104{
105 CK_RV rv;
106 CK_ULONG i;
107
108 debug("pkcs11_provider_finalize: %p refcount %d valid %d",
109 p, p->refcount, p->valid);
110 if (!p->valid)
111 return;
112 for (i = 0; i < p->nslots; i++) {
113 if (p->slotinfo[i].session &&
114 (rv = p->function_list->C_CloseSession(
115 p->slotinfo[i].session)) != CKR_OK)
116 error("C_CloseSession failed: %lu", rv);
117 }
118 if ((rv = p->function_list->C_Finalize(NULL)) != CKR_OK)
119 error("C_Finalize failed: %lu", rv);
120 p->valid = 0;
121 p->function_list = NULL;
122#ifdef HAVE_DLOPEN
123 dlclose(p->handle);
124#endif
125}
126
127/*
128 * remove a reference to the provider.
129 * called when a key gets destroyed or when the provider is unregistered.
130 */
131static void
132pkcs11_provider_unref(struct pkcs11_provider *p)
133{
134 debug("pkcs11_provider_unref: %p refcount %d", p, p->refcount);
135 if (--p->refcount <= 0) {
136 if (p->valid)
137 error("pkcs11_provider_unref: %p still valid", p);
138 free(p->name);
139 free(p->slotlist);
140 free(p->slotinfo);
141 free(p);
142 }
143}
144
145/* unregister all providers, keys might still point to the providers */
146void
147pkcs11_terminate(void)
148{
149 struct pkcs11_provider *p;
150
151 while ((p = TAILQ_FIRST(&pkcs11_providers)) != NULL) {
152 TAILQ_REMOVE(&pkcs11_providers, p, next);
153 pkcs11_provider_finalize(p);
154 pkcs11_provider_unref(p);
155 }
156}
157
158/* lookup provider by name */
159static struct pkcs11_provider *
160pkcs11_provider_lookup(char *provider_id)
161{
162 struct pkcs11_provider *p;
163
164 TAILQ_FOREACH(p, &pkcs11_providers, next) {
165 debug("check %p %s", p, p->name);
166 if (!strcmp(provider_id, p->name))
167 return (p);
168 }
169 return (NULL);
170}
171
172/* unregister provider by name */
173int
174pkcs11_del_provider(char *provider_id)
175{
176 struct pkcs11_provider *p;
177
178 if ((p = pkcs11_provider_lookup(provider_id)) != NULL) {
179 TAILQ_REMOVE(&pkcs11_providers, p, next);
180 pkcs11_provider_finalize(p);
181 pkcs11_provider_unref(p);
182 return (0);
183 }
184 return (-1);
185}

193/* release a wrapped object */
194static void
195pkcs11_k11_free(void *parent, void *ptr, CRYPTO_EX_DATA *ad, int idx,
196 long argl, void *argp)
197{
198 struct pkcs11_key *k11 = ptr;
199
200 debug("%s: parent %p ptr %p idx %d", __func__, parent, ptr, idx);
201 if (k11 == NULL)
202 return;
203 if (k11->provider)
204 pkcs11_provider_unref(k11->provider);
205 free(k11->keyid);
206 free(k11);
207}

209/* find a single 'obj' for given attributes */
210static int
211pkcs11_find(struct pkcs11_provider *p, CK_ULONG slotidx, CK_ATTRIBUTE *attr,
212 CK_ULONG nattr, CK_OBJECT_HANDLE *obj)
213{
214 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f;
215 CK_SESSION_HANDLE session;
216 CK_ULONG nfound = 0;
217 CK_RV rv;
218 int ret = -1;
219
220 f = p->function_list;
221 session = p->slotinfo[slotidx].session;
222 if ((rv = f->C_FindObjectsInit(session, attr, nattr)) != CKR_OK) {
223 error("C_FindObjectsInit failed (nattr %lu): %lu", nattr, rv);
224 return (-1);
225 }
226 if ((rv = f->C_FindObjects(session, obj, 1, &nfound)) != CKR_OK ||
227 nfound != 1) {
228 debug("C_FindObjects failed (nfound %lu nattr %lu): %lu",
229 nfound, nattr, rv);
230 } else
231 ret = 0;
232 if ((rv = f->C_FindObjectsFinal(session)) != CKR_OK)
233 error("C_FindObjectsFinal failed: %lu", rv);
234 return (ret);
235}

237static int
238pkcs11_login(struct pkcs11_key *k11, CK_USER_TYPE type)
239{
240 struct pkcs11_slotinfo *si;
241 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f;
242 char *pin = NULL, prompt[1024];
243 CK_RV rv;
244
245 if (!k11->provider || !k11->provider->valid) {
246 error("no pkcs11 (valid) provider found");
247 return (-1);
248 }
249
250 f = k11->provider->function_list;
251 si = &k11->provider->slotinfo[k11->slotidx];
252
253 if (!pkcs11_interactive) {
254 error("need pin entry%s",
255 (si->token.flags & CKF_PROTECTED_AUTHENTICATION_PATH) ?
256 " on reader keypad" : "");
257 return (-1);
258 }
259 if (si->token.flags & CKF_PROTECTED_AUTHENTICATION_PATH)
260 verbose("Deferring PIN entry to reader keypad.");
261 else {
262 snprintf(prompt, sizeof(prompt), "Enter PIN for '%s': ",
263 si->token.label);
264 if ((pin = read_passphrase(prompt, RP_ALLOW_EOF)) == NULL) {
265 debug("%s: no pin specified", __func__);
266 return (-1); /* bail out */
267 }
268 }
269 rv = f->C_Login(si->session, type, (u_char *)pin,
270 (pin != NULL) ? strlen(pin) : 0);
271 if (pin != NULL)
272 freezero(pin, strlen(pin));
273 if (rv != CKR_OK && rv != CKR_USER_ALREADY_LOGGED_IN) {
274 error("C_Login failed: %lu", rv);
275 return (-1);
276 }
277 si->logged_in = 1;
278 return (0);
279}

281static int
282pkcs11_check_obj_bool_attrib(struct pkcs11_key *k11, CK_OBJECT_HANDLE obj,
283 CK_ATTRIBUTE_TYPE type, int *val)
284{
285 struct pkcs11_slotinfo *si;
286 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f;
287 CK_BBOOL flag = 0;
288 CK_ATTRIBUTE attr;
289 CK_RV rv;
290
291 *val = 0;
292
293 if (!k11->provider || !k11->provider->valid) {
294 error("no pkcs11 (valid) provider found");
295 return (-1);
296 }
297
298 f = k11->provider->function_list;
299 si = &k11->provider->slotinfo[k11->slotidx];
300
301 attr.type = type;
302 attr.pValue = &flag;
303 attr.ulValueLen = sizeof(flag);
304
305 rv = f->C_GetAttributeValue(si->session, obj, &attr, 1);
306 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
307 error("C_GetAttributeValue failed: %lu", rv);
308 return (-1);
309 }
310 *val = flag != 0;
311 debug("%s: provider %p slot %lu object %lu: attrib %lu = %d",
312 __func__, k11->provider, k11->slotidx, obj, type, *val);
313 return (0);
314}

316static int
317pkcs11_get_key(struct pkcs11_key *k11, CK_MECHANISM_TYPE mech_type)
318{
319 struct pkcs11_slotinfo *si;
320 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f;
321 CK_OBJECT_HANDLE obj;
322 CK_RV rv;
323 CK_OBJECT_CLASS private_key_class;
324 CK_BBOOL true_val;
325 CK_MECHANISM mech;
326 CK_ATTRIBUTE key_filter[3];
327 int always_auth = 0;
328 int did_login = 0;
329
330 if (!k11->provider || !k11->provider->valid) {
331 error("no pkcs11 (valid) provider found");
332 return (-1);
333 }
334
335 f = k11->provider->function_list;
336 si = &k11->provider->slotinfo[k11->slotidx];
337
338 if ((si->token.flags & CKF_LOGIN_REQUIRED) && !si->logged_in) {
339 if (pkcs11_login(k11, CKU_USER) < 0) {
340 error("login failed");
341 return (-1);
342 }
343 did_login = 1;
344 }
345
346 memset(&key_filter, 0, sizeof(key_filter));
347 private_key_class = CKO_PRIVATE_KEY;
348 key_filter[0].type = CKA_CLASS;
349 key_filter[0].pValue = &private_key_class;
350 key_filter[0].ulValueLen = sizeof(private_key_class);
351
352 key_filter[1].type = CKA_ID;
353 key_filter[1].pValue = k11->keyid;
354 key_filter[1].ulValueLen = k11->keyid_len;
355
356 true_val = CK_TRUE;
357 key_filter[2].type = CKA_SIGN;
358 key_filter[2].pValue = &true_val;
359 key_filter[2].ulValueLen = sizeof(true_val);
360
361 /* try to find object w/CKA_SIGN first, retry w/o */
362 if (pkcs11_find(k11->provider, k11->slotidx, key_filter, 3, &obj) < 0 &&
363 pkcs11_find(k11->provider, k11->slotidx, key_filter, 2, &obj) < 0) {
364 error("cannot find private key");
365 return (-1);
366 }
367
368 memset(&mech, 0, sizeof(mech));
369 mech.mechanism = mech_type;
370 mech.pParameter = NULL_PTR;
371 mech.ulParameterLen = 0;
372
373 if ((rv = f->C_SignInit(si->session, &mech, obj)) != CKR_OK) {
374 error("C_SignInit failed: %lu", rv);
375 return (-1);
376 }
377
378 pkcs11_check_obj_bool_attrib(k11, obj, CKA_ALWAYS_AUTHENTICATE,
379 &always_auth); /* ignore errors here */
380 if (always_auth && !did_login) {
381 debug("%s: always-auth key", __func__);
382 if (pkcs11_login(k11, CKU_CONTEXT_SPECIFIC) < 0) {
383 error("login failed for always-auth key");
384 return (-1);
385 }
386 }
387
388 return (0);
389}

391/* openssl callback doing the actual signing operation */
392static int
393pkcs11_rsa_private_encrypt(int flen, const u_char *from, u_char *to, RSA *rsa,
394 int padding)
395{
396 struct pkcs11_key *k11;
397 struct pkcs11_slotinfo *si;
398 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f;
399 CK_ULONG tlen = 0;
400 CK_RV rv;
401 int rval = -1;
402
403 if ((k11 = RSA_get_ex_data(rsa, rsa_idx)) == NULL) {
404 error("RSA_get_ex_data failed for rsa %p", rsa);
405 return (-1);
406 }
407
408 if (pkcs11_get_key(k11, CKM_RSA_PKCS) == -1) {
409 error("pkcs11_get_key failed");
410 return (-1);
411 }
412
413 f = k11->provider->function_list;
414 si = &k11->provider->slotinfo[k11->slotidx];
415 tlen = RSA_size(rsa);
416
417 /* XXX handle CKR_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL */
418 rv = f->C_Sign(si->session, __UNCONST(from), flen, to, &tlen);
419 if (rv == CKR_OK)
420 rval = tlen;
421 else
422 error("C_Sign failed: %lu", rv);
423
424 return (rval);
425}

434static int
435pkcs11_rsa_start_wrapper(void)
436{
437 if (rsa_method != NULL)
438 return (0);
439 rsa_method = RSA_meth_dup(RSA_get_default_method());
440 if (rsa_method == NULL)
441 return (-1);
442 rsa_idx = RSA_get_ex_new_index(0, __UNCONST("ssh-pkcs11-rsa"),
443 NULL, NULL, pkcs11_k11_free);
444 if (rsa_idx == -1)
445 return (-1);
446 if (!RSA_meth_set1_name(rsa_method, "pkcs11") ||
447 !RSA_meth_set_priv_enc(rsa_method, pkcs11_rsa_private_encrypt) ||
448 !RSA_meth_set_priv_dec(rsa_method, pkcs11_rsa_private_decrypt)) {
449 error("%s: setup pkcs11 method failed", __func__);
450 return (-1);
451 }
452 return (0);
453}

455/* redirect private key operations for rsa key to pkcs11 token */
456static int
457pkcs11_rsa_wrap(struct pkcs11_provider *provider, CK_ULONG slotidx,
458 CK_ATTRIBUTE *keyid_attrib, RSA *rsa)
459{
460 struct pkcs11_key *k11;
461
462 if (pkcs11_rsa_start_wrapper() == -1)
463 return (-1);
464
465 k11 = xcalloc(1, sizeof(*k11));
466 k11->provider = provider;
467 provider->refcount++; /* provider referenced by RSA key */
468 k11->slotidx = slotidx;
469 /* identify key object on smartcard */
470 k11->keyid_len = keyid_attrib->ulValueLen;
471 if (k11->keyid_len > 0) {
472 k11->keyid = xmalloc(k11->keyid_len);
473 memcpy(k11->keyid, keyid_attrib->pValue, k11->keyid_len);
474 }
475
476 RSA_set_method(rsa, rsa_method);
477 RSA_set_ex_data(rsa, rsa_idx, k11);
478 return (0);
479}

481/* openssl callback doing the actual signing operation */
482static ECDSA_SIG *
483ecdsa_do_sign(const unsigned char *dgst, int dgst_len, const BIGNUM *inv,
484 const BIGNUM *rp, EC_KEY *ec)
485{
486 struct pkcs11_key *k11;
487 struct pkcs11_slotinfo *si;
488 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f;
489 CK_ULONG siglen = 0, bnlen;
490 CK_RV rv;
491 ECDSA_SIG *ret = NULL;
492 u_char *sig;
493 BIGNUM *r = NULL, *s = NULL;
494
495 if ((k11 = EC_KEY_get_ex_data(ec, ec_key_idx)) == NULL) {
496 ossl_error("EC_KEY_get_key_method_data failed for ec");
497 return (NULL);
498 }
499
500 if (pkcs11_get_key(k11, CKM_ECDSA) == -1) {
501 error("pkcs11_get_key failed");
502 return (NULL);
503 }
504
505 f = k11->provider->function_list;
506 si = &k11->provider->slotinfo[k11->slotidx];
507
508 siglen = ECDSA_size(ec);
509 sig = xmalloc(siglen);
510
511 /* XXX handle CKR_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL */
512 rv = f->C_Sign(si->session, __UNCONST(dgst), dgst_len, sig, &siglen);
513 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
514 error("C_Sign failed: %lu", rv);
515 goto done;
516 }
517 if (siglen < 64 || siglen > 132 || siglen % 2) {
518 ossl_error("d2i_ECDSA_SIG failed");
519 goto done;
520 }
521 bnlen = siglen/2;
522 if ((ret = ECDSA_SIG_new()) == NULL) {
523 error("ECDSA_SIG_new failed");
524 goto done;
525 }
526 if ((r = BN_bin2bn(sig, bnlen, NULL)) == NULL ||
527 (s = BN_bin2bn(sig+bnlen, bnlen, NULL)) == NULL) {
528 ossl_error("d2i_ECDSA_SIG failed");
529 ECDSA_SIG_free(ret);
530 ret = NULL;
531 goto done;
532 }
533 if (!ECDSA_SIG_set0(ret, r, s)) {
534 error("%s: ECDSA_SIG_set0 failed", __func__);
535 ECDSA_SIG_free(ret);
536 ret = NULL;
537 goto done;
538 }
539 r = s = NULL; /* now owned by ret */
540 /* success */
541 done:
542 BN_free(r);
543 BN_free(s);
544 free(sig);
545
546 return (ret);
547}

549static int
550pkcs11_ecdsa_start_wrapper(void)
551{
552 int (*orig_sign)(int, const unsigned char *, int, unsigned char *,
553 unsigned int *, const BIGNUM *, const BIGNUM *, EC_KEY *) = NULL;
554
555 if (ec_key_method != NULL)
556 return (0);
557 ec_key_idx = EC_KEY_get_ex_new_index(0, __UNCONST("ssh-pkcs11-ecdsa"),
558 NULL, NULL, pkcs11_k11_free);
559 if (ec_key_idx == -1)
560 return (-1);
561 ec_key_method = EC_KEY_METHOD_new(EC_KEY_OpenSSL());
562 if (ec_key_method == NULL)
563 return (-1);
564 EC_KEY_METHOD_get_sign(ec_key_method, &orig_sign, NULL, NULL);
565 EC_KEY_METHOD_set_sign(ec_key_method, orig_sign, NULL, ecdsa_do_sign);
566 return (0);
567}

593/* remove trailing spaces */
594static void
595rmspace(u_char *buf, size_t len)
596{
597 size_t i;
598
599 if (!len)
600 return;
601 for (i = len - 1; i > 0; i--)
602 if (i == len - 1 || buf[i] == ' ')
603 buf[i] = '\0';
604 else
605 break;
606}

608/*
609 * open a pkcs11 session and login if required.
610 * if pin == NULL we delay login until key use
611 */
612static int
613pkcs11_open_session(struct pkcs11_provider *p, CK_ULONG slotidx, char *pin,
614 CK_ULONG user)
615{
616 struct pkcs11_slotinfo *si;
617 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f;
618 CK_RV rv;
619 CK_SESSION_HANDLE session;
620 int login_required, have_pinpad, ret;
621 char prompt[1024], *xpin = NULL;
622
623 f = p->function_list;
624 si = &p->slotinfo[slotidx];
625
626 have_pinpad = si->token.flags & CKF_PROTECTED_AUTHENTICATION_PATH;
627 login_required = si->token.flags & CKF_LOGIN_REQUIRED;
628
629 /* fail early before opening session */
630 if (login_required && !have_pinpad && !pkcs11_interactive &&
631 (pin == NULL || strlen(pin) == 0)) {
632 error("pin required");
633 return (-SSH_PKCS11_ERR_PIN_REQUIRED);
634 }
635 if ((rv = f->C_OpenSession(p->slotlist[slotidx], CKF_RW_SESSION|
636 CKF_SERIAL_SESSION, NULL, NULL, &session)) != CKR_OK) {
637 error("C_OpenSession failed: %lu", rv);
638 return (-1);
639 }
640 if (login_required) {
641 if (have_pinpad && (pin == NULL || strlen(pin) == 0)) {
642 /* defer PIN entry to the reader keypad */
643 rv = f->C_Login(session, CKU_USER, NULL_PTR, 0);
644 } else {
645 if (pkcs11_interactive) {
646 snprintf(prompt, sizeof(prompt),
647 "Enter PIN for '%s': ", si->token.label);
648 if ((xpin = read_passphrase(prompt,
649 RP_ALLOW_EOF)) == NULL) {
650 debug("%s: no pin specified",
651 __func__);
652 return (-SSH_PKCS11_ERR_PIN_REQUIRED);
653 }
654 pin = xpin;
655 }
656 rv = f->C_Login(session, CKU_USER,
657 (u_char *)pin, strlen(pin));
658 if (xpin != NULL)
659 freezero(xpin, strlen(xpin));
660 }
661 if (rv != CKR_OK && rv != CKR_USER_ALREADY_LOGGED_IN) {
662 error("C_Login failed: %lu", rv);
663 ret = (rv == CKR_PIN_LOCKED) ?
664 -SSH_PKCS11_ERR_PIN_LOCKED :
665 -SSH_PKCS11_ERR_LOGIN_FAIL;
666 if ((rv = f->C_CloseSession(session)) != CKR_OK)
667 error("C_CloseSession failed: %lu", rv);
668 return (ret);
669 }
670 si->logged_in = 1;
671 }
672 si->session = session;
673 return (0);
674}

676static int
677pkcs11_key_included(struct sshkey ***keysp, int *nkeys, struct sshkey *key)
678{
679 int i;
680
681 for (i = 0; i < *nkeys; i++)
682 if (sshkey_equal(key, (*keysp)[i]))
683 return (1);
684 return (0);
685}

687static struct sshkey *
688pkcs11_fetch_ecdsa_pubkey(struct pkcs11_provider *p, CK_ULONG slotidx,
689 CK_OBJECT_HANDLE *obj)
690{
691 CK_ATTRIBUTE key_attr[3];
692 CK_SESSION_HANDLE session;
693 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f = NULL;
694 CK_RV rv;
695 ASN1_OCTET_STRING *octet = NULL;
696 EC_KEY *ec = NULL;
697 EC_GROUP *group = NULL;
698 struct sshkey *key = NULL;
699 const unsigned char *attrp = NULL;
700 int i;
701 int nid;
702
703 memset(&key_attr, 0, sizeof(key_attr));
704 key_attr[0].type = CKA_ID;
705 key_attr[1].type = CKA_EC_POINT;
706 key_attr[2].type = CKA_EC_PARAMS;
707
708 session = p->slotinfo[slotidx].session;
709 f = p->function_list;
710
711 /* figure out size of the attributes */
712 rv = f->C_GetAttributeValue(session, *obj, key_attr, 3);
713 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
714 error("C_GetAttributeValue failed: %lu", rv);
715 return (NULL);
716 }
717
718 /*
719 * Allow CKA_ID (always first attribute) to be empty, but
720 * ensure that none of the others are zero length.
721 * XXX assumes CKA_ID is always first.
722 */
723 if (key_attr[1].ulValueLen == 0 ||
724 key_attr[2].ulValueLen == 0) {
725 error("invalid attribute length");
726 return (NULL);
727 }
728
729 /* allocate buffers for attributes */
730 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
731 if (key_attr[i].ulValueLen > 0)
732 key_attr[i].pValue = xcalloc(1, key_attr[i].ulValueLen);
733
734 /* retrieve ID, public point and curve parameters of EC key */
735 rv = f->C_GetAttributeValue(session, *obj, key_attr, 3);
736 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
737 error("C_GetAttributeValue failed: %lu", rv);
738 goto fail;
739 }
740
741 ec = EC_KEY_new();
742 if (ec == NULL) {
743 error("EC_KEY_new failed");
744 goto fail;
745 }
746
747 attrp = key_attr[2].pValue;
748 group = d2i_ECPKParameters(NULL, &attrp, key_attr[2].ulValueLen);
749 if (group == NULL) {
750 ossl_error("d2i_ECPKParameters failed");
751 goto fail;
752 }
753
754 if (EC_KEY_set_group(ec, group) == 0) {
755 ossl_error("EC_KEY_set_group failed");
756 goto fail;
757 }
758
759 if (key_attr[1].ulValueLen <= 2) {
760 error("CKA_EC_POINT too small");
761 goto fail;
762 }
763
764 attrp = key_attr[1].pValue;
765 octet = d2i_ASN1_OCTET_STRING(NULL, &attrp, key_attr[1].ulValueLen);
766 if (octet == NULL) {
767 ossl_error("d2i_ASN1_OCTET_STRING failed");
768 goto fail;
769 }
770 attrp = octet->data;
771 if (o2i_ECPublicKey(&ec, &attrp, octet->length) == NULL) {
772 ossl_error("o2i_ECPublicKey failed");
773 goto fail;
774 }
775
776 nid = sshkey_ecdsa_key_to_nid(ec);
777 if (nid < 0) {
778 error("couldn't get curve nid");
779 goto fail;
780 }
781
782 if (pkcs11_ecdsa_wrap(p, slotidx, &key_attr[0], ec))
783 goto fail;
784
785 key = sshkey_new(KEY_UNSPEC);
786 if (key == NULL) {
787 error("sshkey_new failed");
788 goto fail;
789 }
790
791 key->ecdsa = ec;
792 key->ecdsa_nid = nid;
793 key->type = KEY_ECDSA;
794 key->flags |= SSHKEY_FLAG_EXT;
795 ec = NULL; /* now owned by key */
796
797fail:
798 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
799 free(key_attr[i].pValue);
800 if (ec)
801 EC_KEY_free(ec);
802 if (group)
803 EC_GROUP_free(group);
804 if (octet)
805 ASN1_OCTET_STRING_free(octet);
806
807 return (key);
808}

810static struct sshkey *
811pkcs11_fetch_rsa_pubkey(struct pkcs11_provider *p, CK_ULONG slotidx,
812 CK_OBJECT_HANDLE *obj)
813{
814 CK_ATTRIBUTE key_attr[3];
815 CK_SESSION_HANDLE session;
816 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f = NULL;
817 CK_RV rv;
818 RSA *rsa = NULL;
819 BIGNUM *rsa_n, *rsa_e;
820 struct sshkey *key = NULL;
821 int i;
822
823 memset(&key_attr, 0, sizeof(key_attr));
824 key_attr[0].type = CKA_ID;
825 key_attr[1].type = CKA_MODULUS;
826 key_attr[2].type = CKA_PUBLIC_EXPONENT;
827
828 session = p->slotinfo[slotidx].session;
829 f = p->function_list;
830
831 /* figure out size of the attributes */
832 rv = f->C_GetAttributeValue(session, *obj, key_attr, 3);
833 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
834 error("C_GetAttributeValue failed: %lu", rv);
835 return (NULL);
836 }
837
838 /*
839 * Allow CKA_ID (always first attribute) to be empty, but
840 * ensure that none of the others are zero length.
841 * XXX assumes CKA_ID is always first.
842 */
843 if (key_attr[1].ulValueLen == 0 ||
844 key_attr[2].ulValueLen == 0) {
845 error("invalid attribute length");
846 return (NULL);
847 }
848
849 /* allocate buffers for attributes */
850 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
851 if (key_attr[i].ulValueLen > 0)
852 key_attr[i].pValue = xcalloc(1, key_attr[i].ulValueLen);
853
854 /* retrieve ID, modulus and public exponent of RSA key */
855 rv = f->C_GetAttributeValue(session, *obj, key_attr, 3);
856 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
857 error("C_GetAttributeValue failed: %lu", rv);
858 goto fail;
859 }
860
861 rsa = RSA_new();
862 if (rsa == NULL) {
863 error("RSA_new failed");
864 goto fail;
865 }
866
867 rsa_n = BN_bin2bn(key_attr[1].pValue, key_attr[1].ulValueLen, NULL);
868 rsa_e = BN_bin2bn(key_attr[2].pValue, key_attr[2].ulValueLen, NULL);
869 if (rsa_n == NULL || rsa_e == NULL) {
870 error("BN_bin2bn failed");
871 goto fail;
872 }
873 if (!RSA_set0_key(rsa, rsa_n, rsa_e, NULL))
874 fatal("%s: set key", __func__);
875 rsa_n = rsa_e = NULL; /* transferred */
876
877 if (pkcs11_rsa_wrap(p, slotidx, &key_attr[0], rsa))
878 goto fail;
879
880 key = sshkey_new(KEY_UNSPEC);
881 if (key == NULL) {
882 error("sshkey_new failed");
883 goto fail;
884 }
885
886 key->rsa = rsa;
887 key->type = KEY_RSA;
888 key->flags |= SSHKEY_FLAG_EXT;
889 rsa = NULL; /* now owned by key */
890
891fail:
892 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
893 free(key_attr[i].pValue);
894 RSA_free(rsa);
895
896 return (key);
897}

899static struct sshkey *
900pkcs11_fetch_x509_pubkey(struct pkcs11_provider *p, CK_ULONG slotidx,
901 CK_OBJECT_HANDLE *obj)
902{
903 CK_ATTRIBUTE cert_attr[3];
904 CK_SESSION_HANDLE session;
905 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f = NULL;
906 CK_RV rv;
907 X509 *x509 = NULL;
908 EVP_PKEY *evp;
909 RSA *rsa = NULL;
910 EC_KEY *ec = NULL;
911 struct sshkey *key = NULL;
912 int i;
913 int nid;
914 const u_char *cp;
915
916 memset(&cert_attr, 0, sizeof(cert_attr));
917 cert_attr[0].type = CKA_ID;
918 cert_attr[1].type = CKA_SUBJECT;
919 cert_attr[2].type = CKA_VALUE;
920
921 session = p->slotinfo[slotidx].session;
922 f = p->function_list;
923
924 /* figure out size of the attributes */
925 rv = f->C_GetAttributeValue(session, *obj, cert_attr, 3);
926 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
927 error("C_GetAttributeValue failed: %lu", rv);
928 return (NULL);
929 }
930
931 /*
932 * Allow CKA_ID (always first attribute) to be empty, but
933 * ensure that none of the others are zero length.
934 * XXX assumes CKA_ID is always first.
935 */
936 if (cert_attr[1].ulValueLen == 0 ||
937 cert_attr[2].ulValueLen == 0) {
938 error("invalid attribute length");
939 return (NULL);
940 }
941
942 /* allocate buffers for attributes */
943 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
944 if (cert_attr[i].ulValueLen > 0)
945 cert_attr[i].pValue = xcalloc(1, cert_attr[i].ulValueLen);
946
947 /* retrieve ID, subject and value of certificate */
948 rv = f->C_GetAttributeValue(session, *obj, cert_attr, 3);
949 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
950 error("C_GetAttributeValue failed: %lu", rv);
951 goto fail;
952 }
953
954 x509 = X509_new();
955 if (x509 == NULL) {
956 error("x509_new failed");
957 goto fail;
958 }
959
960 cp = cert_attr[2].pValue;
961 if (d2i_X509(&x509, &cp, cert_attr[2].ulValueLen) == NULL) {
962 error("d2i_x509 failed");
963 goto fail;
964 }
965
966 evp = X509_get_pubkey(x509);
967 if (evp == NULL) {
968 error("X509_get_pubkey failed");
969 goto fail;
970 }
971
972 if (EVP_PKEY_base_id(evp) == EVP_PKEY_RSA) {
973 if (EVP_PKEY_get0_RSA(evp) == NULL) {
974 error("invalid x509; no rsa key");
975 goto fail;
976 }
977 if ((rsa = RSAPublicKey_dup(EVP_PKEY_get0_RSA(evp))) == NULL) {
978 error("RSAPublicKey_dup failed");
979 goto fail;
980 }
981
982 if (pkcs11_rsa_wrap(p, slotidx, &cert_attr[0], rsa))
983 goto fail;
984
985 key = sshkey_new(KEY_UNSPEC);
986 if (key == NULL) {
987 error("sshkey_new failed");
988 goto fail;
989 }
990
991 key->rsa = rsa;
992 key->type = KEY_RSA;
993 key->flags |= SSHKEY_FLAG_EXT;
994 rsa = NULL; /* now owned by key */
995 } else if (EVP_PKEY_base_id(evp) == EVP_PKEY_EC) {
996 if (EVP_PKEY_get0_EC_KEY(evp) == NULL) {
997 error("invalid x509; no ec key");
998 goto fail;
999 }
1000 if ((ec = EC_KEY_dup(EVP_PKEY_get0_EC_KEY(evp))) == NULL) {
1001 error("EC_KEY_dup failed");
1002 goto fail;
1003 }
1004
1005 nid = sshkey_ecdsa_key_to_nid(ec);
1006 if (nid < 0) {
1007 error("couldn't get curve nid");
1008 goto fail;
1009 }
1010
1011 if (pkcs11_ecdsa_wrap(p, slotidx, &cert_attr[0], ec))
1012 goto fail;
1013
1014 key = sshkey_new(KEY_UNSPEC);
1015 if (key == NULL) {
1016 error("sshkey_new failed");
1017 goto fail;
1018 }
1019
1020 key->ecdsa = ec;
1021 key->ecdsa_nid = nid;
1022 key->type = KEY_ECDSA;
1023 key->flags |= SSHKEY_FLAG_EXT;
1024 ec = NULL; /* now owned by key */
1025 } else
1026 error("unknown certificate key type");
1027
1028fail:
1029 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
1030 free(cert_attr[i].pValue);
1031 X509_free(x509);
1032 RSA_free(rsa);
1033 EC_KEY_free(ec);
1034
1035 return (key);
1036}

1049/*
1050 * lookup certificates for token in slot identified by slotidx,
1051 * add 'wrapped' public keys to the 'keysp' array and increment nkeys.
1052 * keysp points to an (possibly empty) array with *nkeys keys.
1053 */
1054static int
1055pkcs11_fetch_certs(struct pkcs11_provider *p, CK_ULONG slotidx,
1056 struct sshkey ***keysp, int *nkeys)
1057{
1058 struct sshkey *key = NULL;
1059 CK_OBJECT_CLASS key_class;
1060 CK_ATTRIBUTE key_attr[1];
1061 CK_SESSION_HANDLE session;
1062 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f = NULL;
1063 CK_RV rv;
1064 CK_OBJECT_HANDLE obj;
1065 CK_ULONG n = 0;
1066 int ret = -1;
1067
1068 memset(&key_attr, 0, sizeof(key_attr));
1069 memset(&obj, 0, sizeof(obj));
1070
1071 key_class = CKO_CERTIFICATE;
1072 key_attr[0].type = CKA_CLASS;
1073 key_attr[0].pValue = &key_class;
1074 key_attr[0].ulValueLen = sizeof(key_class);
1075
1076 session = p->slotinfo[slotidx].session;
1077 f = p->function_list;
1078
1079 rv = f->C_FindObjectsInit(session, key_attr, 1);
1080 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
1081 error("C_FindObjectsInit failed: %lu", rv);
1082 goto fail;
1083 }
1084
1085 while (1) {
1086 CK_CERTIFICATE_TYPE ck_cert_type;
1087
1088 rv = f->C_FindObjects(session, &obj, 1, &n);
1089 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
1090 error("C_FindObjects failed: %lu", rv);
1091 goto fail;
1092 }
1093 if (n == 0)
1094 break;
1095
1096 memset(&ck_cert_type, 0, sizeof(ck_cert_type));
1097 memset(&key_attr, 0, sizeof(key_attr));
1098 key_attr[0].type = CKA_CERTIFICATE_TYPE;
1099 key_attr[0].pValue = &ck_cert_type;
1100 key_attr[0].ulValueLen = sizeof(ck_cert_type);
1101
1102 rv = f->C_GetAttributeValue(session, obj, key_attr, 1);
1103 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
1104 error("C_GetAttributeValue failed: %lu", rv);
1105 goto fail;
1106 }
1107
1108 switch (ck_cert_type) {
1109 case CKC_X_509:
1110 key = pkcs11_fetch_x509_pubkey(p, slotidx, &obj);
1111 break;
1112 default:
1113 /* XXX print key type? */
1114 key = NULL;
1115 error("skipping unsupported certificate type");
1116 }
1117
1118 if (key == NULL) {
1119 error("failed to fetch key");
1120 continue;
1121 }
1122
1123 if (pkcs11_key_included(keysp, nkeys, key)) {
1124 sshkey_free(key);
1125 } else {
1126 /* expand key array and add key */
1127 *keysp = xrecallocarray(*keysp, *nkeys,
1128 *nkeys + 1, sizeof(struct sshkey *));
1129 (*keysp)[*nkeys] = key;
1130 *nkeys = *nkeys + 1;
1131 debug("have %d keys", *nkeys);
1132 }
1133 }
1134
1135 ret = 0;
1136fail:
1137 rv = f->C_FindObjectsFinal(session);
1138 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
1139 error("C_FindObjectsFinal failed: %lu", rv);
1140 ret = -1;
1141 }
1142
1143 return (ret);
1144}

1146/*
1147 * lookup public keys for token in slot identified by slotidx,
1148 * add 'wrapped' public keys to the 'keysp' array and increment nkeys.
1149 * keysp points to an (possibly empty) array with *nkeys keys.
1150 */
1151static int
1152pkcs11_fetch_keys(struct pkcs11_provider *p, CK_ULONG slotidx,
1153 struct sshkey ***keysp, int *nkeys)
1154{
1155 struct sshkey *key = NULL;
1156 CK_OBJECT_CLASS key_class;
1157 CK_ATTRIBUTE key_attr[1];
1158 CK_SESSION_HANDLE session;
1159 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f = NULL;
1160 CK_RV rv;
1161 CK_OBJECT_HANDLE obj;
1162 CK_ULONG n = 0;
1163 int ret = -1;
1164
1165 memset(&key_attr, 0, sizeof(key_attr));
1166 memset(&obj, 0, sizeof(obj));
1167
1168 key_class = CKO_PUBLIC_KEY;
1169 key_attr[0].type = CKA_CLASS;
1170 key_attr[0].pValue = &key_class;
1171 key_attr[0].ulValueLen = sizeof(key_class);
1172
1173 session = p->slotinfo[slotidx].session;
1174 f = p->function_list;
1175
1176 rv = f->C_FindObjectsInit(session, key_attr, 1);
1177 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
1178 error("C_FindObjectsInit failed: %lu", rv);
1179 goto fail;
1180 }
1181
1182 while (1) {
1183 CK_KEY_TYPE ck_key_type;
1184
1185 rv = f->C_FindObjects(session, &obj, 1, &n);
1186 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
1187 error("C_FindObjects failed: %lu", rv);
1188 goto fail;
1189 }
1190 if (n == 0)
1191 break;
1192
1193 memset(&ck_key_type, 0, sizeof(ck_key_type));
1194 memset(&key_attr, 0, sizeof(key_attr));
1195 key_attr[0].type = CKA_KEY_TYPE;
1196 key_attr[0].pValue = &ck_key_type;
1197 key_attr[0].ulValueLen = sizeof(ck_key_type);
1198
1199 rv = f->C_GetAttributeValue(session, obj, key_attr, 1);
1200 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
1201 error("C_GetAttributeValue failed: %lu", rv);
1202 goto fail;
1203 }
1204
1205 switch (ck_key_type) {
1206 case CKK_RSA:
1207 key = pkcs11_fetch_rsa_pubkey(p, slotidx, &obj);
1208 break;
1209 case CKK_ECDSA:
1210 key = pkcs11_fetch_ecdsa_pubkey(p, slotidx, &obj);
1211 break;
1212 default:
1213 /* XXX print key type? */
1214 key = NULL;
1215 error("skipping unsupported key type");
1216 }
1217
1218 if (key == NULL) {
1219 error("failed to fetch key");

1225 } else {
1226 /* expand key array and add key */
1227 *keysp = xrecallocarray(*keysp, *nkeys,
1228 *nkeys + 1, sizeof(struct sshkey *));
1229 (*keysp)[*nkeys] = key;
1230 *nkeys = *nkeys + 1;
1231 debug("have %d keys", *nkeys);
1232 }
1233 }
1234
1235 ret = 0;
1236fail:
1237 rv = f->C_FindObjectsFinal(session);
1238 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
1239 error("C_FindObjectsFinal failed: %lu", rv);
1240 ret = -1;
1241 }
1242
1243 return (ret);
1244}

1250static struct sshkey *
1251pkcs11_rsa_generate_private_key(struct pkcs11_provider *p, CK_ULONG slotidx,
1252 char *label, CK_ULONG bits, CK_BYTE keyid, u_int32_t *err)
1253{

1277 sizeof(false_val));
1278 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_WRAP, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));
1279 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_DERIVE, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));
1280 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_MODULUS_BITS, &bits, sizeof(bits));
1281 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_PUBLIC_EXPONENT, pubExponent,

1283 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_ID, &keyid, sizeof(keyid));
1284
1285 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_TOKEN, &true_val, sizeof(true_val));
1286 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_LABEL, plabel, strlen(plabel));
1287 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_PRIVATE, &true_val, sizeof(true_val));
1288 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_SENSITIVE, &true_val, sizeof(true_val));
1289 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_DECRYPT, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));
1290 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_SIGN, &true_val, sizeof(true_val));

1293 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_UNWRAP, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));
1294 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_DERIVE, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));

1300

1302 &pubKey, &privKey)) != CKR_OK) {
1303 error("%s: key generation failed: error 0x%lx", __func__, rv);
1304 *err = rv;
1305 return NULL;
1306 }
1307
1308 return pkcs11_fetch_rsa_pubkey(p, slotidx, &pubKey);
1309}

1311static int
1312pkcs11_decode_hex(const char *hex, unsigned char **dest, size_t *rlen)
1313{
1314 size_t i, len;
1315 char ptr[3];
1316
1317 if (dest)
1318 *dest = NULL;
1319 if (rlen)
1320 *rlen = 0;
1321
1322 if ((len = strlen(hex)) % 2)
1323 return -1;
1324 len /= 2;
1325
1326 *dest = xmalloc(len);
1327
1328 ptr[2] = '\0';
1329 for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
1330 ptr[0] = hex[2 * i];
1331 ptr[1] = hex[(2 * i) + 1];
1332 if (!isxdigit(ptr[0]) || !isxdigit(ptr[1]))
1333 return -1;
1334 (*dest)[i] = (unsigned char)strtoul(ptr, NULL, 16);
1335 }
1336
1337 if (rlen)
1338 *rlen = len;
1339
1340 return 0;
1341}

1359 struct pkcs11_slotinfo *si;
1360 char *plabel = label ? label : "";
1361 int i;
1362 size_t ecparams_size;
1363 unsigned char *ecparams = NULL;
1364 int npub = 0, npriv = 0;
1365 CK_RV rv;
1366 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f;
1367 CK_SESSION_HANDLE session;
1368 CK_BBOOL true_val = CK_TRUE, false_val = CK_FALSE;
1369 CK_OBJECT_HANDLE pubKey, privKey;
1370 CK_MECHANISM mech = {
1371 CKM_EC_KEY_PAIR_GEN, NULL_PTR, 0
1372 };
1373 CK_ATTRIBUTE tpub[16], tpriv[16];
1374
1375 *err = 0;
1376
1377 for (i = 0; ec_curve_infos[i].name; i++) {
1378 if (ec_curve_infos[i].size == bits)
1379 break;
1380 }
1381 if (!ec_curve_infos[i].name) {
1382 error("%s: invalid key size %lu", __func__, bits);
1383 return NULL;
1384 }
1385 if (pkcs11_decode_hex(ec_curve_infos[i].oid_encoded, &ecparams,
1386 &ecparams_size) == -1) {
1387 error("%s: invalid oid", __func__);
1388 return NULL;
1389 }
1390
1391 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_TOKEN, &true_val, sizeof(true_val));
1392 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_LABEL, plabel, strlen(plabel));
1393 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_ENCRYPT, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));
1394 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_VERIFY, &true_val, sizeof(true_val));
1395 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_VERIFY_RECOVER, &false_val,
1396 sizeof(false_val));
1397 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_WRAP, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));
1398 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_DERIVE, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));
1399 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_EC_PARAMS, ecparams, ecparams_size);
1400 FILL_ATTR(tpub, npub, CKA_ID, &keyid, sizeof(keyid));
1401
1402 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_TOKEN, &true_val, sizeof(true_val));
1403 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_LABEL, plabel, strlen(plabel));
1404 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_PRIVATE, &true_val, sizeof(true_val));
1405 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_SENSITIVE, &true_val, sizeof(true_val));
1406 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_DECRYPT, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));
1407 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_SIGN, &true_val, sizeof(true_val));
1408 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_SIGN_RECOVER, &false_val,
1409 sizeof(false_val));
1410 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_UNWRAP, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));
1411 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_DERIVE, &false_val, sizeof(false_val));
1412 FILL_ATTR(tpriv, npriv, CKA_ID, &keyid, sizeof(keyid));
1413
1414 f = p->function_list;
1415 si = &p->slotinfo[slotidx];
1416 session = si->session;
1417
1418 if ((rv = f->C_GenerateKeyPair(session, &mech, tpub, npub, tpriv, npriv,
1419 &pubKey, &privKey)) != CKR_OK) {
1420 error("%s: key generation failed: error 0x%lx", __func__, rv);
1421 *err = rv;
1422 return NULL;
1423 }
1424
1425 return pkcs11_fetch_ecdsa_pubkey(p, slotidx, &pubKey);
1426}
1427#endif /* WITH_PKCS11_KEYGEN */

1429/*
1430 * register a new provider, fails if provider already exists. if
1431 * keyp is provided, fetch keys.
1432 */
1433static int
1434pkcs11_register_provider(char *provider_id, char *pin, struct sshkey ***keyp,
1435 struct pkcs11_provider **providerp, CK_ULONG user)
1436{
1437 int nkeys, need_finalize = 0;
1438 int ret = -1;
1439 struct pkcs11_provider *p = NULL;
1440 void *handle = NULL;
1441 CK_RV (*getfunctionlist)(CK_FUNCTION_LIST **);
1442 CK_RV rv;
1443 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f = NULL;
1444 CK_TOKEN_INFO *token;
1445 CK_ULONG i;
1446
1447 if (providerp == NULL)
1448 goto fail;
1449 *providerp = NULL;
1450
1451 if (keyp != NULL)
1452 *keyp = NULL;
1453
1454 if (pkcs11_provider_lookup(provider_id) != NULL) {
1455 debug("%s: provider already registered: %s",
1456 __func__, provider_id);
1457 goto fail;
1458 }
1459 /* open shared pkcs11-library */
1460 if ((handle = dlopen(provider_id, RTLD_NOW)) == NULL) {
1461 error("dlopen %s failed: %s", provider_id, dlerror());
1462 goto fail;
1463 }
1464 if ((getfunctionlist = dlsym(handle, "C_GetFunctionList")) == NULL) {
1465 error("dlsym(C_GetFunctionList) failed: %s", dlerror());
1466 goto fail;
1467 }
1468 p = xcalloc(1, sizeof(*p));
1469 p->name = xstrdup(provider_id);
1470 p->handle = handle;
1471 /* setup the pkcs11 callbacks */
1472 if ((rv = (*getfunctionlist)(&f)) != CKR_OK) {
1473 error("C_GetFunctionList for provider %s failed: %lu",
1474 provider_id, rv);
1475 goto fail;
1476 }
1477 p->function_list = f;
1478 if ((rv = f->C_Initialize(NULL)) != CKR_OK) {
1479 error("C_Initialize for provider %s failed: %lu",
1480 provider_id, rv);
1481 goto fail;
1482 }
1483 need_finalize = 1;
1484 if ((rv = f->C_GetInfo(&p->info)) != CKR_OK) {
1485 error("C_GetInfo for provider %s failed: %lu",
1486 provider_id, rv);
1487 goto fail;
1488 }
1489 rmspace(p->info.manufacturerID, sizeof(p->info.manufacturerID));
1490 rmspace(p->info.libraryDescription, sizeof(p->info.libraryDescription));
1491 debug("provider %s: manufacturerID <%s> cryptokiVersion %d.%d"
1492 " libraryDescription <%s> libraryVersion %d.%d",
1493 provider_id,
1494 p->info.manufacturerID,
1495 p->info.cryptokiVersion.major,
1496 p->info.cryptokiVersion.minor,
1497 p->info.libraryDescription,
1498 p->info.libraryVersion.major,
1499 p->info.libraryVersion.minor);
1500 if ((rv = f->C_GetSlotList(CK_TRUE, NULL, &p->nslots)) != CKR_OK) {
1501 error("C_GetSlotList failed: %lu", rv);
1502 goto fail;
1503 }
1504 if (p->nslots == 0) {
1505 error("%s: provider %s returned no slots", __func__,
1506 provider_id);
1507 ret = -SSH_PKCS11_ERR_NO_SLOTS;
1508 goto fail;
1509 }
1510 p->slotlist = xcalloc(p->nslots, sizeof(CK_SLOT_ID));
1511 if ((rv = f->C_GetSlotList(CK_TRUE, p->slotlist, &p->nslots))
1512 != CKR_OK) {
1513 error("C_GetSlotList for provider %s failed: %lu",
1514 provider_id, rv);
1515 goto fail;
1516 }
1517 p->slotinfo = xcalloc(p->nslots, sizeof(struct pkcs11_slotinfo));
1518 p->valid = 1;
1519 nkeys = 0;
1520 for (i = 0; i < p->nslots; i++) {
1521 token = &p->slotinfo[i].token;
1522 if ((rv = f->C_GetTokenInfo(p->slotlist[i], token))
1523 != CKR_OK) {
1524 error("C_GetTokenInfo for provider %s slot %lu "
1525 "failed: %lu", provider_id, (unsigned long)i, rv);
1526 continue;
1527 }
1528 if ((token->flags & CKF_TOKEN_INITIALIZED) == 0) {
1529 debug2("%s: ignoring uninitialised token in "
1530 "provider %s slot %lu", __func__,
1531 provider_id, (unsigned long)i);
1532 continue;
1533 }
1534 rmspace(token->label, sizeof(token->label));
1535 rmspace(token->manufacturerID, sizeof(token->manufacturerID));
1536 rmspace(token->model, sizeof(token->model));
1537 rmspace(token->serialNumber, sizeof(token->serialNumber));
1538 debug("provider %s slot %lu: label <%s> manufacturerID <%s> "
1539 "model <%s> serial <%s> flags 0x%lx",
1540 provider_id, (unsigned long)i,
1541 token->label, token->manufacturerID, token->model,
1542 token->serialNumber, token->flags);
1543 /*
1544 * open session, login with pin and retrieve public
1545 * keys (if keyp is provided)
1546 */
1547 if ((ret = pkcs11_open_session(p, i, pin, user)) == 0) {
1548 if (keyp == NULL)
1549 continue;
1550 pkcs11_fetch_keys(p, i, keyp, &nkeys);
1551 pkcs11_fetch_certs(p, i, keyp, &nkeys);
1552 }
1553 }
1554
1555 /* now owned by caller */
1556 *providerp = p;
1557
1558 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&pkcs11_providers, p, next);
1559 p->refcount++; /* add to provider list */
1560
1561 return (nkeys);
1562fail:
1563 if (need_finalize && (rv = f->C_Finalize(NULL)) != CKR_OK)
1564 error("C_Finalize for provider %s failed: %lu",
1565 provider_id, rv);
1566 if (p) {
1567 free(p->name);
1568 free(p->slotlist);
1569 free(p->slotinfo);
1570 free(p);
1571 }
1572 if (handle)
1573 dlclose(handle);
1574 return (ret);
1575}
1576
1577/*
1578 * register a new provider and get number of keys hold by the token,
1579 * fails if provider already exists
1580 */
1581int
1582pkcs11_add_provider(char *provider_id, char *pin, struct sshkey ***keyp)
1583{
1584 struct pkcs11_provider *p = NULL;
1585 int nkeys;
1586
1587 nkeys = pkcs11_register_provider(provider_id, pin, keyp, &p, CKU_USER);
1588
1589 /* no keys found or some other error, de-register provider */
1590 if (nkeys <= 0 && p != NULL) {
1591 TAILQ_REMOVE(&pkcs11_providers, p, next);
1592 pkcs11_provider_finalize(p);
1593 pkcs11_provider_unref(p);
1594 }
1595 if (nkeys == 0)
1596 debug("%s: provider %s returned no keys", __func__,
1597 provider_id);
1598
1599 return (nkeys);
1600}

1603struct sshkey *
1604pkcs11_gakp(char *provider_id, char *pin, unsigned int slotidx, char *label,
1605 unsigned int type, unsigned int bits, unsigned char keyid, u_int32_t *err)
1606{
1607 struct pkcs11_provider *p = NULL;
1608 struct pkcs11_slotinfo *si;
1609 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f;
1610 CK_SESSION_HANDLE session;
1611 struct sshkey *k = NULL;
1612 int ret = -1, reset_pin = 0, reset_provider = 0;
1613 CK_RV rv;
1614
1615 *err = 0;
1616
1617 if ((p = pkcs11_provider_lookup(provider_id)) != NULL)
1618 debug("%s: provider \"%s\" available", __func__, provider_id);
1619 else if ((ret = pkcs11_register_provider(provider_id, pin, NULL, &p,
1620 CKU_SO)) < 0) {
1621 debug("%s: could not register provider %s", __func__,
1622 provider_id);
1623 goto out;
1624 } else
1625 reset_provider = 1;
1626
1627 f = p->function_list;
1628 si = &p->slotinfo[slotidx];
1629 session = si->session;
1630
1631 if ((rv = f->C_SetOperationState(session , pin, strlen(pin),
1632 CK_INVALID_HANDLE, CK_INVALID_HANDLE)) != CKR_OK) {
1633 debug("%s: could not supply SO pin: %lu", __func__, rv);
1634 reset_pin = 0;
1635 } else
1636 reset_pin = 1;
1637
1638 switch (type) {
1639 case KEY_RSA:
1640 if ((k = pkcs11_rsa_generate_private_key(p, slotidx, label,
1641 bits, keyid, err)) == NULL) {
1642 debug("%s: failed to generate RSA key", __func__);
1643 goto out;
1644 }
1645 break;
1646 case KEY_ECDSA:
1647 if ((k = pkcs11_ecdsa_generate_private_key(p, slotidx, label,
1648 bits, keyid, err)) == NULL) {
1649 debug("%s: failed to generate ECDSA key", __func__);
1650 goto out;
1651 }
1652 break;
1653 default:
1654 *err = SSH_PKCS11_ERR_GENERIC;
1655 debug("%s: unknown type %d", __func__, type);
1656 goto out;
1657 }
1658
1659out:
1660 if (reset_pin)
1661 f->C_SetOperationState(session , NULL, 0, CK_INVALID_HANDLE,
1662 CK_INVALID_HANDLE);
1663
1664 if (reset_provider)
1665 pkcs11_del_provider(provider_id);
1666
1667 return (k);
1668}

1670struct sshkey *
1671pkcs11_destroy_keypair(char *provider_id, char *pin, unsigned long slotidx,
1672 unsigned char keyid, u_int32_t *err)
1673{
1674 struct pkcs11_provider *p = NULL;
1675 struct pkcs11_slotinfo *si;
1676 struct sshkey *k = NULL;
1677 int reset_pin = 0, reset_provider = 0;
1678 CK_ULONG nattrs;
1679 CK_FUNCTION_LIST *f;
1680 CK_SESSION_HANDLE session;
1681 CK_ATTRIBUTE attrs[16];
1682 CK_OBJECT_CLASS key_class;
1683 CK_KEY_TYPE key_type;
1684 CK_OBJECT_HANDLE obj = CK_INVALID_HANDLE;
1685 CK_RV rv;
1686
1687 *err = 0;
1688
1689 if ((p = pkcs11_provider_lookup(provider_id)) != NULL) {
1690 debug("%s: using provider \"%s\"", __func__, provider_id);
1691 } else if (pkcs11_register_provider(provider_id, pin, NULL, &p,
1692 CKU_SO) < 0) {
1693 debug("%s: could not register provider %s", __func__,
1694 provider_id);
1695 goto out;
1696 } else
1697 reset_provider = 1;
1698
1699 f = p->function_list;
1700 si = &p->slotinfo[slotidx];
1701 session = si->session;
1702
1703 if ((rv = f->C_SetOperationState(session , pin, strlen(pin),
1704 CK_INVALID_HANDLE, CK_INVALID_HANDLE)) != CKR_OK) {
1705 debug("%s: could not supply SO pin: %lu", __func__, rv);
1706 reset_pin = 0;
1707 } else
1708 reset_pin = 1;
1709
1710 /* private key */
1711 nattrs = 0;
1712 key_class = CKO_PRIVATE_KEY;
1713 FILL_ATTR(attrs, nattrs, CKA_CLASS, &key_class, sizeof(key_class));
1714 FILL_ATTR(attrs, nattrs, CKA_ID, &keyid, sizeof(keyid));
1715
1716 if (pkcs11_find(p, slotidx, attrs, nattrs, &obj) == 0 &&
1717 obj != CK_INVALID_HANDLE) {
1718 if ((rv = f->C_DestroyObject(session, obj)) != CKR_OK) {
1719 debug("%s: could not destroy private key 0x%hhx",
1720 __func__, keyid);
1721 *err = rv;
1722 goto out;
1723 }
1724 }
1725
1726 /* public key */
1727 nattrs = 0;
1728 key_class = CKO_PUBLIC_KEY;
1729 FILL_ATTR(attrs, nattrs, CKA_CLASS, &key_class, sizeof(key_class));
1730 FILL_ATTR(attrs, nattrs, CKA_ID, &keyid, sizeof(keyid));
1731
1732 if (pkcs11_find(p, slotidx, attrs, nattrs, &obj) == 0 &&
1733 obj != CK_INVALID_HANDLE) {
1734
1735 /* get key type */
1736 nattrs = 0;
1737 FILL_ATTR(attrs, nattrs, CKA_KEY_TYPE, &key_type,
1738 sizeof(key_type));
1739 rv = f->C_GetAttributeValue(session, obj, attrs, nattrs);
1740 if (rv != CKR_OK) {
1741 debug("%s: could not get key type of public key 0x%hhx",
1742 __func__, keyid);
1743 *err = rv;
1744 key_type = -1;
1745 }
1746 if (key_type == CKK_RSA)
1747 k = pkcs11_fetch_rsa_pubkey(p, slotidx, &obj);
1748 else if (key_type == CKK_ECDSA)
1749 k = pkcs11_fetch_ecdsa_pubkey(p, slotidx, &obj);
1750
1751 if ((rv = f->C_DestroyObject(session, obj)) != CKR_OK) {
1752 debug("%s: could not destroy public key 0x%hhx",
1753 __func__, keyid);
1754 *err = rv;
1755 goto out;
1756 }
1757 }
1758
1759out:
1760 if (reset_pin)
1761 f->C_SetOperationState(session , NULL, 0, CK_INVALID_HANDLE,
1762 CK_INVALID_HANDLE);
1763
1764 if (reset_provider)
1765 pkcs11_del_provider(provider_id);
1766
1767 return (k);
1768}

1775 return (-1);
